{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/debut-theme-show-slideshow-text-inside-image-on-mobile","result":{"pageContext":{"id":1248,"date":"2021-11-13T03:45:58","date_gmt":"2021-11-13T03:45:58","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=1248"},"modified":"2022-05-07T09:47:50","modified_gmt":"2022-05-07T09:47:50","slug":"debut-theme-show-slideshow-text-inside-image-on-mobile","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/debut-theme-show-slideshow-text-inside-image-on-mobile/","title":{"rendered":"Debut theme: display text inside of the slideshow on mobile"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Debut theme&#8217;s slideshow section, on mobile, by default, will move all text outside of it, making it show up right below the slideshow. <br><br>Today I&#8217;ll be teaching you how to edit it with CSS code so the text shows up on top of the images, making it behave the same way it does on desktop.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-making-a-backup-first\">Making a backup first</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before diving into the tutorial make sure you download the theme, so in case you face any issues you can easily revert back.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1514\" height=\"481\" class=\"wp-image-503\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png 1514w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-600x191.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-1200x381.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1514px) 100vw, 1514px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-finding-the-css-file-to-add-the-code\">Finding the CSS file to add the code</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>From your Shopify admin, go to&nbsp;<strong>Online Store</strong>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Themes&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Actions&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Edit Code</strong>.</li><li>Find&nbsp;the file named <strong>theme.scss.liquid, theme.css.liquid </strong>or <strong>theme.css</strong>. The name varies depending on the version of your theme.</li><li>Scroll down to the very bottom of the file, paste the following code and save:<br><br>[gist]8df5519215d19c080d697902d48276e0[gist]<br></li><li>It should look something like this:<br><br></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1117\" height=\"831\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/image.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1249\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/image.png 1117w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/image-850x632.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/image-768x571.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1117px) 100vw, 1117px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-understanding-the-code-and-how-to-adapt-it-to-your-needs\">Understanding the code and how to adapt it to your needs</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some key features that you can adjust in the code above:<br><br>32px = the title font size on mobile<br>15px = the subtitle font size on mobile<br>#000 = hex color of the overlay on top of the images. Darkening the image will make it easier to read the text inside of it<br>0.25 = the intensity of the overlay color. If you don&#8217;t want to use any overlay, you can use <strong>0.0</strong>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-conclusion\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>That is it, you&#8217;re good to go! <br><br>It&#8217;s still important to keep in mind that Debut&#8217;s slideshow comes with several limitations, like cutting off images on mobile and desktop. <br><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/add-slideshow-shopify-no-apps\">Click here</a> to read our other tutorial to learn how to fix the aforementioned issues and add more features to your Debut theme&#8217;s slideshow.  </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"you-may-also-like\">You may also like</h3>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"custom-you-may-also-like\">Here are some other tutorials you may be interested in:<br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/debut-shopify-theme-how-to-add-swipe-for-product-page-images\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Add arrows &amp; swiping to Debut product pages<span><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media3.giphy.com/media/3EkLfaQZ4YQKaZ26OY/giphy.gif\"></span></a><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/debut-theme-product-page-images-zoom-tutorial\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Debut &#8220;click to zoom&#8221; lightbox tutorial: mobile friendly images, slider &amp; arrows<span><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media1.giphy.com/media/WR5Yl3hW8x6aUilwRe/giphy.gif\"></span></a><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/how-to-disable-right-click-image-and-text-copying-without-apps\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Improve your website&#8217;s safety: block right click, image copying and more</a></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn how to display the Debut theme&#8217;s slideshow text on top of the images on mobile.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1252,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[157],"image_alt":"","featured_image_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/debut_slideshow-850x478.png","featured_image_small_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/debut_slideshow-200x200.png","featured_image_large_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/debut_slideshow-1200x675.png","categories_names":["Blog"],"acf":[],"tag_names":["debut theme"],"featured_image_url":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/debut_slideshow.png","featured_image_url_alt":"","_li